Ruth Hiatt https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruth_Hiatt 0 Ruth Hiatt (January 6, 1906 – April 21, 1994) was an actress in motion pictures beginning in the silent film era. She is known for performing in 1920s comedies directed by Jack White, Norman Taurog, and Mack Sennett.
